race.comment: METALLIC RULER (1) has been solid in two runs back from a spell, finding the line nicely behind a smart winner at Cranbourne last time out to grab second when well supported. Comes back a notch in grade now and should take plenty of beating. TWO SIGMA (13) hasn't been beaten far in two runs back and did get a long way back from the wide gate at Cranbourne when last seen. She can land closer here with the light weight and the rise to 1400m suits much better. SO SUAVE (7) resumes having gone to the paddock a maiden winner at Doomben over 2070m. He may need further than this being a full brother to champion mare Verry Elleegant but can be staying on strongly late. DUAL AWARD (6) is lightly raced resuming for his second campaign. Williams on from a good gate helps. HOMEWARD (10) has won two in a row and deserves a shot in town.
